<h1>Learn about crypto and how to invest</h1>

<h2>What is cryptocurrency?</h2>
<p>Cryptocurrency is a digital or virtual currency that handles the creation of new units and verifies and secures transactions by using cryptography. It operates independently from a central bank and can be transferred directly between individuals without intermediairies like banks.
    It is decentralized and transparent, transactions are recorded on a blockchain which is essentially a public ledger.
    There are many types of cryptocurrency in circulation, the most popular being Bitcoin, each with their own unique features and uses.
</p>
